Make the inside of a 3D object hollow.

Remove volume from a 3-dimensional shape such that a wall of the
provided thickness remains around the exterior of the shape.

```kcl
hollow(
  @solid: Solid,
  thickness: number(Length),
): Solid
```


### Arguments

| Name | Type | Description | Required |
|----------|------|-------------|----------|
| `solid` | [`Solid`](/docs/kcl/types/std-types-Solid) | Which solid to hollow out | Yes |
| `thickness` | `number(Length)` | The thickness of the remaining shell | Yes |

### Returns

[`Solid`](/docs/kcl/types/std-types-Solid)


### Examples

```kcl
// Hollow a basic sketch.
firstSketch = startSketchOn(XY)
    |> startProfile(at = [-12, 12])
    |> line(end = [24, 0])
    |> line(end = [0, -24])
    |> line(end = [-24, 0])
    |> close()
    |> extrude(length = 6)
    |> hollow (thickness = 0.25)
```
